# Lutherie TODO

## UI

### Layout
- GraphPanel defaults to central widget but can be docked/moved freely
- Add "open editor" button to ComponentParameters (and node right click context menu) that launches specialized widget as a floating KDDW::DockWidget

### Components
- Expose Min/Max/Default parameters via right click tool window
- Prevent modules from spawning on top of each other
- Move add logic to toolbar menu with hotkeys for quick-add context menu
- Component duplication — plain copy, and copy-with-connections

### Sequencer
- Per-note velocity support
- Shift+scroll for horizontal scrollbar
- Prevent note creation while engine is running
- On sequencer status toggle, send note-off for all active notes (or disallow toggling during run)

## Signal Flow

### Control Connections
- create boolean control port signal/trigger system
  - hard sync ( phase cycle complete signal, phase reset trigger)

### Macro Knobs
- Macro Knob panel docked to edge of graph panel, moves with it
- Modulation socket on each macro knob
- Macro Edit Mode: indicator appears next to each control panel parameter, drag to assign to macro knob
- Indicator outside of Macro Edit Mode showing a macro is assigned (same style as MIDI indicator)
- Arbitrary functions to apply value from macro knob to control knob, listed below the macro knob
  
### MIDI Control Mapping
- Right click context menu on parameter widget to map to MIDI control
- Continuous variables: generate wiggle to map
- Discrete variables: map on button press count with configurable threshold
- Warn if continuous mode sees no continuous values coming in (and vice versa)
- Indicator on parameter showing MIDI association, hover to reveal control id

### Peripheral Devices
- match audio output to the number of ports on the peripheral device
- allow for multiple midi peripheral devices
- support midi output peripherals
  
## Components to Add
